      <originalsloc id="aspace_c40dd1128a3ee0b3d725978697dfb262">
         <head>Existence and Location of Originals</head>
         <p>The entire collection can be located in the Samuel Wells Williams Family Papers (MS 547).   The papers include correspondence (comprising over half of the collection), manuscripts of Samuel Wells Williams's Syllabic Dictionary of the Chinese Language, themes and lecture notes by Frederick Wells Williams, diaries, newspaper clippings, articles on China, maps, and pictures. The bulk of the correspondence relates to S.W. Williams, missionary, diplomat, and sinologue.</p>
         <p>HM 22 only consists of: Correspondence and related papers, 1853-1854, of Samuel Wells Williams regarding his services as an interpreter of Commodore Matthew Perry's expedition to Japan</p>
         <p>HM 277 only consists of: Series I. Correspondence, 1824-1939. A Guide to the content of the reels comprising HM277 is available.</p>  
      </originalsloc>
